{"pageProps":{"data":{"id":112910,"date":"2021-03-03T10:23:54","date_gmt":"2021-03-03T15:23:54","guid":{"rendered":"https://blog.ted.com/?p=112910"},"modified":"2021-03-03T11:09:40","modified_gmt":"2021-03-03T16:09:40","slug":"a-ted-series-takes-a-look-at-the-link-between-your-money-and-your-mind","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://blog.ted.com/a-ted-series-takes-a-look-at-the-link-between-your-money-and-your-mind/","title":{"rendered":"A TED series takes a look at the link between your money and your mind"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"https://www.ted.com/series/your_money_and_your_mind\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-112911 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED_Money_Mind_1600x480-01.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1600\" height=\"480\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED_Money_Mind_1600x480-01.jpg 1600w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED_Money_Mind_1600x480-01.jpg?resize=150,45 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED_Money_Mind_1600x480-01.jpg?resize=250,75 250w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED_Money_Mind_1600x480-01.jpg?resize=768,230 768w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED_Money_Mind_1600x480-01.jpg?resize=530,159 530w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED_Money_Mind_1600x480-01.jpg?resize=1536,461 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Have you ever painstakingly crafted a budget only to wildly overspend on your next outing? Or bought something that you instantly regretted but couldn&#8217;t return? Managing your money can get complicated &#8212; but it doesn&#8217;t have to be.</p>\n<p>In TED&#8217;s video series <a href=\"https://www.ted.com/series/your_money_and_your_mind\"><em>Your Money and Your Mind with Wendy De La Rosa</em></a>, behavioral economist Wendy De La Rosa explains why we spend too much and save too little (even when we know better) &#8212; and shares easy steps and practical tips to help you achieve a more secure financial future.</p>\n<p>In eight brief, informative episodes, De La Rosa explores the tricky relationship between human behavior and money. Considering the psychological, emotional, cultural and social factors that influence money decisions, she walks you through how to gain control over your finances, so you can gain peace of mind.</p>\n<p>De La Rosa sheds light on <a href=\"https://www.ted.com/talks/wendy_de_la_rosa_why_we_make_bad_financial_choices_even_when_we_know_better\">the purchases we often end up regretting</a> and explains <a href=\"https://www.ted.com/talks/wendy_de_la_rosa_can_t_stick_to_a_budget_try_these_tweaks_instead\">why traditional budgets don&#8217;t work for most people</a>. She offers <a href=\"https://www.ted.com/talks/wendy_de_la_rosa_the_money_talk_that_every_couple_needs_to_have\">a guide on how to talk about money with your partner</a>, <a href=\"https://www.ted.com/talks/wendy_de_la_rosa_pay_off_your_credit_cards_faster_with_these_4_easy_changes\">4 steps to pay off your credit card debt faster</a>, <a href=\"https://www.ted.com/talks/wendy_de_la_rosa_3_sneaky_tactics_that_websites_use_to_make_you_spend\">3 ways to evade the sneaky (borderline predatory) practices of websites</a> and a <a href=\"https://www.ted.com/talks/wendy_de_la_rosa_a_simple_2_step_plan_for_saving_more_money\">2-step plan on saving more money.</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>What purchases do we often regret? And why do we keep buying them?</p>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Wendy De La Rosa: Why we make bad financial choices -- even when we know better\" src=\"https://embed.ted.com/talks/wendy_de_la_rosa_why_we_make_bad_financial_choices_even_when_we_know_better\" width=\"586\" height=\"330\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s why (and how) you should talk to your partner about money:</p>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Wendy De La Rosa: The money talk that every couple needs to have\" src=\"https://embed.ted.com/talks/wendy_de_la_rosa_the_money_talk_that_every_couple_needs_to_have\" width=\"586\" height=\"330\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s not you, it&#8217;s your budget. Do this instead:</p>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Wendy De La Rosa: Can&#039;t stick to a budget? Try these tweaks instead\" src=\"https://embed.ted.com/talks/wendy_de_la_rosa_can_t_stick_to_a_budget_try_these_tweaks_instead\" width=\"586\" height=\"330\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>4 ways to get out from under your credit card debit:</p>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Wendy De La Rosa: Pay off your credit cards faster with these 4 easy changes\" src=\"https://embed.ted.com/talks/wendy_de_la_rosa_pay_off_your_credit_cards_faster_with_these_4_easy_changes\" width=\"586\" height=\"330\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Are you saving? Good. Here&#8217;s how to save more:</p>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Wendy De La Rosa: A simple 2-step plan for saving more money\" src=\"https://embed.ted.com/talks/wendy_de_la_rosa_a_simple_2_step_plan_for_saving_more_money\" width=\"586\" height=\"330\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Websites are sneaky. Be sneakier:</p>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Wendy De La Rosa: 3 sneaky tactics that websites use to make you spend\" src=\"https://embed.ted.com/talks/wendy_de_la_rosa_3_sneaky_tactics_that_websites_use_to_make_you_spend\" width=\"586\" height=\"330\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Keeping up with the Joneses might actually be good for your wallet:</p>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Wendy De La Rosa: Why talking to your friends can help you save money\" src=\"https://embed.ted.com/talks/wendy_de_la_rosa_why_talking_to_your_friends_can_help_you_save_money\" width=\"586\" height=\"330\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Take a financial health day and complete these 10 easy steps:</p>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Wendy De La Rosa: 10 steps to boost your financial health -- that you can do in a day\" src=\"https://embed.ted.com/talks/wendy_de_la_rosa_10_steps_to_boost_your_financial_health_that_you_can_do_in_a_day\" width=\"586\" height=\"330\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen></iframe></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Have you ever painstakingly crafted a budget only to wildly overspend on your next outing? Or bought something that you instantly regretted but couldn&#8217;t return? Managing your money can get complicated &#8212; but it doesn&#8217;t have to be. In TED&#8217;s video series Your Money and Your Mind with Wendy De La Rosa, behavioral economist Wendy <a class=\"read-more\" title=\"Read more\" href=\"https://blog.ted.com/a-ted-series-takes-a-look-at-the-link-between-your-money-and-your-mind/\">[<span>&hellip;</span>]</a></p>\n","protected":false},"author":173426824,"featured_media":112928,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"amp_status":"","spay_email":""},"categories":[75292],"tags":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/YourMoneyYourMind_2021V_E07-embed.jpg","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://blog.ted.com/wp-json/wp/v2